Description - External

&lt;p&gt;Therapy Assistant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spot Salary Dependant on Experience &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FTC Until March 21. Part time and Full Time Available&lt;br /&gt;Ormskirk. West Lancashire&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Therapy Assistant or Assistant Practitioner based in the Ormskirk area? Are you looking to join an NHS Health and Social Care partner which is striving to make positive changes? Would you like to work for an organisation where more than 9 out of every 10 of the people who use services would recommend them?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Valued&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; As a Therpay Assistant delivering NHS services with us you will receive a spot salary dependant on experience - including group pension. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will become part of the Virgin Tribe. This grants you access to premier offers on Virgin Products such as gyms, media and much more..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll access our central online health and lifestyle platform covering healthy recipes, activity challenges, and support information around mental health.&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel Proud&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have an NVQ Level 3 in Healthcare or equivalent training and development. You will be competent in carrying out basic functional assessments and be able to demonstrate tact and empathy in a clinical/team setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is community based involving visits to patients in their own homes and travelling to clinics so transportation and the ability to transport equipment is required. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; As the Therapy Assistantyou will provide support to the Rehabilitation Service in delivering the required range of clinical interventions and support to pateints. This will include providing administration support to clinicians, taking responsibility for own clinical caseload, undertake assessent, treatments and interventions as required and to participate in audit and service development. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Feel the Difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’d like to discuss the role further, or request the full job description, please contact Sarah Lunt via email: Sarah.Lunt&lt;em&gt;@virgincare.co.uk&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We partner with the NHS to make a real difference to people and we’re building a working environment where colleagues too can really feel the difference. It’s the kind of place where nothing’s too much trouble. Where you’ll feel empowered, listened to, valued and where we’ll support you to bring your best self to work every single day and to deliver high quality care. And that’s just the beginning. Since 2006, we’ve delivered services to millions of people by developing our own unique approach where our patients are at the centre of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a Disability Confident Committed company, we work in partnership with the Department of Work and Pensions (DWP) to provide facilities, work environment adjustments and technical solutions to make our business an inclusive place for all.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We’re committed to equal opportunities and welcome a broad diversity of talent to apply. We reserve the right to cease any advertising prior to the published closing date for a role that receives a high number of applications. Virgin Care Limited, its subsidiary companies and the Virgin Care LLPs are part of the Virgin Group and provide NHS and social care services. If you would like to know a little more about how we use your information, please see our website’s privacy policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
